HONG KONG, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government said on Sunday that it will slaughter all chickens in local chicken farms and all poultry at wholesale markets and retail outlets in an attempt to get rid of the source of influenza A H5N1 virus or "bird flu."
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Experts with China's National Influenza Center confirmed that no cases of H5N1 virus infection have been discovered in the inland areas, even though the strain has been detected a small group of Hong Kong residents.
